---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SiteNav from '../components/SiteNav.astro';
---

<Layout title="My Skill Development Journey">
<div class="journey-page">

<!-- SHARED NAV -->
<SiteNav active="/journey" />

<!-- push content below fixed nav -->
<div style="height:64px;"></div>

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="hero-icon">
      <svg width="48" height="48" viewBox="0 0 48 48" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <rect x="4" y="10" width="40" height="28" rx="3" stroke="#000" stroke-width="2" fill="none"/>
        <path d="M14 20l6 5-6 5M22 30h12" stroke="#000" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
      </svg>
    </div>
    <h1 class="hero-title">My Skill Development Journey 🚀</h1>
    <div class="hero-divider"></div>
    <p class="hero-quote">"Every expert was once a beginner. This journey represents my commitment to continuous learning, innovation, and becoming a world-class software engineer."</p>
    <div class="hero-meta">
      <span class="meta-tag">Software Engineering</span>
      <span class="meta-tag">AI &amp; Technology</span>
      <span class="meta-tag">Personal Growth</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- INTRODUCTION -->
<section class="section fade-section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <p class="section-label">001 — Introduction</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Where It All Begins</h2>
    <div class="intro-body">
      <p>I recently joined a <strong>Skill Development Center</strong> with one goal: to become someone who doesn't just consume technology — but creates it. From day one, this program has been pushing me to grow across every dimension that matters as an engineer.</p>
      <p>It's about building deep <strong>technical knowledge</strong>, sharpening <strong>programming skills</strong>, unlocking <strong>creativity</strong>, and developing rock-solid <strong>problem-solving</strong> instincts. But the scope goes far beyond code.</p>
      <p>This journey is reshaping how I <strong>communicate ideas</strong>, how I approach challenges with a <strong>professional mindset</strong>, and how I show up every single day. It is teaching me discipline, building my confidence, and nurturing a deep curiosity about what's possible when you combine technology with human ingenuity.</p>
      <p>What follows is the honest, unfiltered story of that journey — day by day, lesson by lesson.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="skills-grid">
      <div class="skill-chip">⚙️ Technical Knowledge</div>
      <div class="skill-chip">💻 Programming Skills</div>
      <div class="skill-chip">🎨 Creativity</div>
      <div class="skill-chip">🗣️ Communication</div>
      <div class="skill-chip">🔍 Problem Solving</div>
      <div class="skill-chip">🎯 Professional Mindset</div>
      <div class="skill-chip">🤝 Teamwork</div>
      <div class="skill-chip">🧠 Curiosity</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- DAY 1 TIMELINE -->
<section class="section section-alt fade-section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <p class="section-label">002 — Timeline</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Day 1 — Defining My Dreams</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">The first day set the tone for everything that followed. Instead of a typical orientation, we were asked a disruptive question: <em>What do you actually want to become?</em></p>
    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>Dream Beyond Academics</h3>
          <p>We were encouraged to think past grades and exams. The session pushed us to imagine our ideal future — not the safe version, but the ambitious one. What kind of engineer? What kind of life?</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>Discussing Future Goals</h3>
          <p>We shared our goals openly — from building AI startups to cracking top product companies. Hearing everyone's ambitions made the room electric. It was a reminder that we were all here for something bigger.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>First Practical Activity — Personal Portfolio</h3>
          <p>Our very first hands-on task was building a personal portfolio website using <strong>Replit</strong>. Not a template — a real, designed-by-us representation of who we are.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>What the Portfolio Represents</h3>
          <p>The portfolio wasn't just a website. It captured our personality, ambitions, interests, projects, and future vision. It forced us to answer: <em>Who am I as a developer? What do I stand for?</em></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-dot last"></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>The Real Lesson — Personal Branding</h3>
          <p>I learned that in the real world, your work has to speak for itself — and a portfolio is how it does that. Building one on day one planted the seed of professional thinking early.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- MOVIES -->
<section class="section fade-section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <p class="section-label">003 — Inspiration</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Movies That Shaped My Thinking</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">Great films don't just entertain — they rewire how you see the world. These are the movies that shifted my perspective on technology, intelligence, and human ambition.</p>
    <div class="media-grid">

      <div class="media-card">
        <div class="poster-wrap">
          <img src="https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYTViNzMxZjEtZGEwNy00MDNiLWIzNGQtZDY2MjQ1OWViZjFmXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzkwMjQ5NzM@._V1_SX120.jpg" alt="Terminator poster" class="poster" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="media-info">
          <h3 class="media-title">The Terminator</h3>
          <div class="media-meta"><span>1984</span><span class="dot">·</span><span>Sci-Fi / Action</span></div>
          <p class="media-desc">A cyborg assassin is sent from the future to eliminate the mother of humanity's future savior, raising profound questions about machine consciousness.</p>
          <div class="learned-box">
            <p class="learned-label">What I Learned</p>
            <p>AI without ethics is dangerous. It taught me that engineers bear moral responsibility for what they build — technology must serve humanity, never dominate it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="media-card">
        <div class="poster-wrap">
          <img src="https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTczNTI2ODUwOF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwMTU0NTIzMw@@._V1_SX120.jpg" alt="Iron Man poster" class="poster" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="media-info">
          <h3 class="media-title">Iron Man</h3>
          <div class="media-meta"><span>2008</span><span class="dot">·</span><span>Sci-Fi / Action</span></div>
          <p class="media-desc">A billionaire engineer builds a powered suit of armor and transforms himself from weapons dealer to a global protector using innovation as his superpower.</p>
          <div class="learned-box">
            <p class="learned-label">What I Learned</p>
            <p>Engineering is a superpower. Tony Stark showed me that technical mastery combined with entrepreneurial thinking can literally change the world.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="media-card">
        <div class="poster-wrap">
          <img src="https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNmE1OWI2ZGItMDUyOS00MmU5LWE0MzEtYzFhZWRlNDIxZjIzXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMDM2NDM2MQ@@._V1_SX120.jpg" alt="I Robot poster" class="poster" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="media-info">
          <h3 class="media-title">I, Robot</h3>
          <div class="media-meta"><span>2004</span><span class="dot">·</span><span>Sci-Fi / Thriller</span></div>
          <p class="media-desc">In a future where robots serve humans, one detective suspects a robot of committing murder — challenging the boundaries of programmed logic versus free will.</p>
          <div class="learned-box">
            <p class="learned-label">What I Learned</p>
            <p>Robots and AI systems will be only as ethical as the rules we program into them. It deepened my interest in AI safety and algorithmic decision-making.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="media-card">
        <div class="poster-wrap">
          <img src="https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTc2MTQ3MDA1Nl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODA3OTI4NjE@._V1_SX120.jpg" alt="The Martian poster" class="poster" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="media-info">
          <h3 class="media-title">The Martian</h3>
          <div class="media-meta"><span>2015</span><span class="dot">·</span><span>Sci-Fi / Drama</span></div>
          <p class="media-desc">An astronaut stranded alone on Mars uses science, ingenuity, and relentless optimism to survive and signal for rescue against impossible odds.</p>
          <div class="learned-box">
            <p class="learned-label">What I Learned</p>
            <p>Science and perseverance solve seemingly impossible problems. It reinforced the engineering mindset: break any problem into smaller solvable steps.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="media-card">
        <div class="poster-wrap">
          <img src="https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNDc4MThhN2EtZjMxNS00NjMyLWJhNWEtMDlmYjNjYzIwNTUxXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNDk3NzU2MTQ@._V1_SX120.jpg" alt="The Big Short poster" class="poster" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="media-info">
          <h3 class="media-title">The Big Short</h3>
          <div class="media-meta"><span>2015</span><span class="dot">·</span><span>Drama / Finance</span></div>
          <p class="media-desc">A group of unconventional investors predict and profit from the 2008 housing market collapse by seeing patterns others were too complacent to notice.</p>
          <div class="learned-box">
            <p class="learned-label">What I Learned</p>
            <p>Data tells the truth even when people ignore it. It sparked my interest in fintech, algorithmic trading, and the power of independent analytical thinking.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="media-card">
        <div class="poster-wrap">
          <img src="https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMzY2ODk4NmUtOTVmNi00ZTdkLTkzNWQtMjc3ZGI2YmI1NGQzXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzkwMjQ5NzM@._V1_SX120.jpg" alt="Star Trek poster" class="poster" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="media-info">
          <h3 class="media-title">Star Trek</h3>
          <div class="media-meta"><span>2009</span><span class="dot">·</span><span>Sci-Fi / Adventure</span></div>
          <p class="media-desc">A young James Kirk rises to captain the USS Enterprise, uniting a diverse crew of brilliant minds to explore the galaxy and face an enemy from the future.</p>
          <div class="learned-box">
            <p class="learned-label">What I Learned</p>
            <p>Diversity of thought makes teams stronger. Leadership isn't about title — it's about vision. Science and exploration are humanity's highest callings.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="media-card">
        <div class="poster-wrap">
          <img src="https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BOTA5NjhiOTAtZWM0ZC00MWNhLThiMzEtZDFkOTk2OTU1ZDJkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTA4NDI1NTQx._V1_SX120.jpg" alt="Star Wars poster" class="poster" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="media-info">
          <h3 class="media-title">Star Wars</h3>
          <div class="media-meta"><span>1977</span><span class="dot">·</span><span>Sci-Fi / Epic</span></div>
          <p class="media-desc">A farm boy from a desert planet discovers his destiny among rebels fighting against a tyrannical galactic empire, guided by an ancient energy called the Force.</p>
          <div class="learned-box">
            <p class="learned-label">What I Learned</p>
            <p>Every expert starts as a nobody. The journey matters more than the destination. Mentorship, purpose, and believing in yourself are the foundations of any great story.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TV SERIES -->
<section class="section section-alt fade-section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <p class="section-label">004 — Series</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Series Worth Watching</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">One series stands out as essential viewing for every aspiring developer and entrepreneur.</p>
    <div class="media-grid media-grid-single">

      <div class="media-card media-card-wide">
        <div class="poster-wrap">
          <img src="https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BOTRlNWZkNzktZjEyMy00MzRkLWI3OGMtZmQ3NDhmZGJjZTQ2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNTQ4NTc5OTU@._V1_SX120.jpg" alt="Silicon Valley poster" class="poster" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="media-info">
          <h3 class="media-title">Silicon Valley</h3>
          <div class="media-meta"><span>2014–2019</span><span class="dot">·</span><span>Comedy / Tech Drama</span></div>
          <p class="media-desc">A group of misfit programmers at a startup incubator navigate the chaotic, cutthroat world of Silicon Valley while trying to launch a revolutionary compression algorithm. Brutal, funny, and painfully accurate.</p>
          <div class="learned-box">
            <p class="learned-label">Lessons for Developers &amp; Entrepreneurs</p>
            <p>Building a startup is 10% idea and 90% execution, politics, and surviving failure. The show demystifies the tech industry — product-market fit is everything, hiring matters more than funding, and pivoting is often survival. It also captures the importance of technical depth: the best engineer in the room almost always wins.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ANIME -->
<section class="section fade-section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <p class="section-label">005 — Anime</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Anime Every Tech Enthusiast Should Watch</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">Don't underestimate anime. These three series contain more genuine life philosophy and engineering thinking than most textbooks.</p>
    <div class="media-grid">

      <div class="media-card">
        <div class="poster-wrap">
          <img src="https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZmEzN2YzOTItMDI5MS00MGU4LWI1NWQtOTg5ZThhNGQwYTEzXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNTA4NTI0OTM@._V1_SX120.jpg" alt="Fullmetal Alchemist Brotherhood poster" class="poster" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="media-info">
          <h3 class="media-title">Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood</h3>
          <div class="media-meta"><span>2009</span><span class="dot">·</span><span>Action / Fantasy</span></div>
          <p class="media-desc">Two brothers use the science of alchemy to search for the Philosopher's Stone after a failed experiment costs them everything — exploring sacrifice, ethics, and the price of ambition.</p>
          <div class="learned-box">
            <p class="learned-label">Why I Recommend It</p>
            <p>The law of Equivalent Exchange — "to obtain something, you must give something of equal value" — is the most honest description of learning I've ever encountered. It shaped how I think about effort, cost, and reward in engineering.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="media-card">
        <div class="poster-wrap">
          <img src="https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNjRiNmNjMmMtN2U2Yi00ODgxLTk3OTMtMmI1MTI1NjYyZTEzXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjAwNDUxODI@._V1_SX120.jpg" alt="Death Note poster" class="poster" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="media-info">
          <h3 class="media-title">Death Note</h3>
          <div class="media-meta"><span>2006</span><span class="dot">·</span><span>Thriller / Psychological</span></div>
          <p class="media-desc">A brilliant student discovers a supernatural notebook that kills anyone whose name is written in it, and begins a cat-and-mouse game with the world's greatest detective.</p>
          <div class="learned-box">
            <p class="learned-label">Why I Recommend It</p>
            <p>A masterclass in systems thinking, logical deduction, and strategic planning. It taught me that intelligence is nothing without ethics — and that the most dangerous person in any room is the one who thinks three steps ahead.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="media-card">
        <div class="poster-wrap">
          <img src="https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BODc5YTBhMTItMjhkZC00Y2IzLWI3MDgtNzgzMzAyNzc0ZjMzXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjAwNDUxODI@._V1_SX120.jpg" alt="Avatar The Last Airbender poster" class="poster" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="media-info">
          <h3 class="media-title">Avatar: The Last Airbender</h3>
          <div class="media-meta"><span>2005</span><span class="dot">·</span><span>Adventure / Fantasy</span></div>
          <p class="media-desc">A young Avatar must master all four elements to bring peace to a world ravaged by war — a story about growth, identity, compassion, and the weight of responsibility.</p>
          <div class="learned-box">
            <p class="learned-label">Why I Recommend It</p>
            <p>Mastery requires breadth and depth. Aang's journey of learning each element mirrors a developer learning new domains. The series celebrates curiosity, humility, resilience, and the courage to keep going even when the task feels impossible.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- DAY 2 TOOLS -->
